Date: 19/8/1905
Source: NZ Truth
Author:
Vol / Page: 9/1/8
Edition:
Quote: The word very often used (perhaps invented) by <i>Truth </i>1905-10 =prohibitionist, `wowser' as a derogatory term, and revived in the mid-30's by Hon. R. Semple, Minister of Works, as a picturesque and derogatory term for croaking complainants: -<i> `sniffling snufflebusters' </i>became popularly associated with Mr Semple's styles of speech
